opicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528072\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gxk1665702877857.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gxk1665702877857.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gxk1665702877857.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gxk1665702877857\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Character Set Packing Codes\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__character_set_packing_codes_94230\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> packing code is used for characters in Uniface installable character sets.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28883e1_d28884e1_d28885e1\">Each entity has a character set used for storing the entity in the database. By default, this is the character set selected during installation, but it can also be a character set specified in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Character Set</span> of the Entity's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span>, or using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> assignment setting (if <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Character Set</span> = <code class=\"ph codeph\">(default)</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28886e1_d28887e1_d28888e1\">Fields with a String data type can contain characters in the entity character set. They can have the following packing codes:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__li_d14648e1_d14649e1_d14650e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> or\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> packing code <p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28889e1_d28890e1_d28891e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> means that\n               the maximum number of characters is <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>. However, if this String is\n               used for holding double-byte characters, only <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>/<code class=\"ph codeph\">2</code>\n               characters can be held. Therefore <code class=\"ph codeph\">C1</code> cannot be used for double-byte\n               characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28892e1_d28893e1_d28894e1\">On a Windows platform, any characters can be\n               entered into a <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> String field, but characters that do not belong to\n               the entity character set cause field validation to fail.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28895e1_d28896e1_d28897e1\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Wide Character\n                  Behavior</span> property of the Entity's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database\n                  Interface</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Character Set</code>, the\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code becomes a <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> packing code.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__note_w8559ab1b5b7b1c11_w8560ab1b5b7b1_w8561ab1b5b7_w8562ab1b5_w8563ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> iSeries systems predominantly use the DB2 database.For more\n               information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"awm1665702727177.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/awm1665702727177.html\" title=\"Uniface data types and packing codes are mapped to DB2 storage formats.\">DB2 Data Packing</a>. </div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__li_d14651e1_d14652e1_d14653e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">U</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> packing code\n               <p class=\"p\" id=\"gxk1665702877857__p_d28898e1_d28899e1_d28900e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">U*</code> packing code can contain\n               characters in its entity character set if the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$META_IN_TRX</span>\n               assignment setting is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jpa1665702722765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jpa1665702722765.html\" title=\"Set the data storage format of String fields with the U* packing code to XML or TRX.\">$META_IN_TRX</a>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzj1665702875634.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Character Packing Code (C)</a><p>The C packing code is used for String data types.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/otr1665702875565.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>TRX Character Packing Codes (U, VU, and SU)</a><p>The U, VU, and SU packing codes should be specified for any data that is to be stored in the Uniface transfer format (TRX). TRX has not been used since Uniface 8, so these packing codes are only available to ensure compatibility with older applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528072\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528072\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Character Set Packing Codes Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Character Set Packing Codes The C packing code is used for characters in Uniface installable character sets. Each entity has a character set used for storing the entity in the database. By default, this is the character set selected during installation, but it can also be a character set specified in the Character Set of the Entity's Database Interface , or using the $DEF_CHARSET assignment setting (if Character Set = (default) . Fields with a String data type can contain characters in the entity character set. They can have the following packing codes: C or C n packing code C n means that the maximum number of characters is n . However, if this String is used for holding double-byte characters, only n / 2 characters can be held. Therefore C1 cannot be used for double-byte characters. On a Windows platform, any characters can be entered into a C String field, but characters that do not belong to the entity character set cause field validation to fail. If the Wide Character Behavior property of the Entity's Database Interface is set to Character Set , the W packing code becomes a C packing code. Note: iSeries systems predominantly use the DB2 database.For more information, see DB2 Data Packing . U n packing code The U* packing code can contain characters in its entity character set if the $META_IN_TRX assignment setting is set to 1 . For more information, see $META_IN_TRX . Related Links Character Packing Code (C) The C packing code is used for String data types. TRX Character Packing Codes (U, VU, and SU) The U, VU, and SU packing codes should be specified for any data that is to be stored in the Uniface transfer format (TRX). TRX has not been used since Uniface 8, so these packing codes are only available to ensure compatibility with older applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}